{"pageProps":{"data":{"news_id":"687","news_catgory":"1","hot_news":"0","news_push":"","news_on_top":"1","news_title":"NASA研究：南極融冰速度歷史新高 年注滿上億奧運泳池","news_summary":"","image_path":"","news_des":null,"news_content":"<p><img alt='' src='/user_files/news_files/%E5%8D%97%E6%A5%B5%E8%9E%8D%E5%86%B0.jpg' style='width: 600px; height: 400px;' /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'>南極融冰速度持續加劇，已達歷史新高。（路透）</span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span lang='EN-US' style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span lang='EN-US' style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'>2020-05-02 15:01:57</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>〔即時新聞／綜合報導〕氣候暖化持續對全球造成影響，美國太空總署（<span lang='EN-US'>NASA</span>）一項新研究表明，目前極地冰融速度已達到歷史新高點，南極洲與格陵蘭每年融化的冰可填滿約<span lang='EN-US'>1</span>億<span lang='EN-US'>2700</span>萬個奧運標準泳池。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>根據《<span lang='EN-US'>CNN</span>》報導，<span lang='EN-US'>NASA</span>這項新研究<span lang='EN-US'>30</span>日發表在國際權威期刊《科學》雜誌，科學家發現，南極洲與格陵蘭州每年分別融化<span lang='EN-US'>1180</span>億噸與<span lang='EN-US'>2000</span>億噸的冰水進入海中，導致海平面從<span lang='EN-US'>2003</span>年至<span lang='EN-US'>2019</span>年間上升了約<span lang='EN-US'>1.3</span>公分，而當前融冰的速度更是來到新高點。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>研究將持續飆高的融冰速度歸因於夏季均溫升高，偏高的溫度導致冰川與冰蓋的固態水持續融化，進而構成促使更多冰融化的正回饋條件。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>研究主要作者，美國華盛頓大學冰川學家史密斯（<span lang='EN-US'>Ben Smith</span>）表示，經過長達<span lang='EN-US'>16</span>年的觀察與研究，科學家現已可確定持續不斷加劇的冰融狀況，與長期氣候變化有關。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'>資料來源<span lang='EN-US'>: https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/3152768</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n","keyword":"","news_order_id":"0","create_date":"2020-05-06","clk_count":"99"}},"__N_SSG":true}